item.title: Loader Files And Runescape JS5 file(im not sure but i think its the new deob) :)
item.dc:creator: @defyboy defyboy
item.description:
@defyboy wrote:

They are one of jagex’s own filetypes (the type you see in the cache) Basically a collection of files appended to each other with 9 byte headers. I have extracted 3 files from it and attached.

Dont have a clue what they do, but the second one is interesting…, The large one looks similar to the files I see in the cachefile all the time, in cache index 10.

The ladder also leads to runescape.pack200 which is just a pack200.GZ file with the first 2 bytes removed (check my sig)
